# ✅ Example 2: Using Cookies in React with `js-cookie` (BEST PRACTICE)

### Why use `js-cookie`?

✔ Cleaner API  
✔ Less bug‑prone  
✔ Industry common

***

## ✅ Install

```bash
npm install js-cookie
```

***

## ✅ Basic usage

```jsx
import Cookies from "js-cookie";
```

***

## ✅ Store cookie

```jsx
Cookies.set("theme", "dark", {
  expires: 7,
  path: "/",
  sameSite: "lax"
});
```

***

## ✅ Read cookie

```jsx
const theme = Cookies.get("theme");
console.log(theme); // dark
```

***

## ✅ Delete cookie

```jsx
Cookies.remove("theme");
```

***

## ✅ Full React Example (Preferred Way)

```jsx
import Cookies from "js-cookie";
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

export default function App() {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState("light");

  useEffect(() => {
    const savedTheme = Cookies.get("theme");
    if (savedTheme) setTheme(savedTheme);
  }, []);

  const toggleTheme = () => {
    const newTheme = theme === "light" ? "dark" : "light";
    Cookies.set("theme", newTheme, { expires: 7, sameSite: "lax" });
    setTheme(newTheme);
  };

  return (
    <div style={{ background: theme === "dark" ? "#222" : "#fff", height: "100vh" }}>
      <h1>{theme.toUpperCase()} MODE</h1>
      <button onClick={toggleTheme}>Toggle Theme</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

✅ Clean  
✅ Readable  
✅ Production friendly

